1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:41,880
It's…

2
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,080
Didn't you say
you wanted to live independently?

3
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,600
- You're yelling now?
- Trai!

4
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,800
Hey, stop!

5
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,040
Money!

6
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:58,240
If Trai never liked your business
and loves his freedom so much,

7
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,520
why don't you just let him go?

8
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:02,040
He's my son. He has to come back here.

9
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,680
But I'm not as good
at making money as Pakbung.

10
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:06,760
How could she think about money
with every breath?

11
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:09,160
You're only good at making money.

12
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,080
Why don't you try getting a man?

13
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:14,920
<i>Your mom didn't die here, right?</i>

14
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,440
<i>And no kids died here either, did they?</i>

15
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,480
You wanna meet them?

16
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,480
100 for each clear glass.
500 for each wine glass.

17
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,800
Break it and you pay.

18
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:27,160
Stingy.

19
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,480
Dad?

20
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,400
Let's get it started.

21
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:33,480
Happy birthday.

22
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,040
Thanks.

23
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,080
Having fun?

24
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,560
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

25
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,400
Where were we?

26
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,880
Does saying sorry fix anything?

27
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,600
We were having fun,
and now, it's all ruined.

28
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:59,160
Sorry. I'm sorry, miss.

29
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,320
Niuniu, what happened?

30
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:02,800
Oh, no.

31
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,360
Petch, I didn't mean to.

32
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,280
Her friend was dancing and bumped into me.

33
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,440
Are you blaming my friend?

34
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,000
Ms. Mika.

35
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:16,360
I sincerely apologize.

36
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:19,680
My staff wasn't careful enough.

37
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:22,600
How about I take the dress to be cleaned?

38
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:26,000
No need. It's dirty.
I'm not going to wear it anymore.

39
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:29,920
That's good. Yeah.

40
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:34,480
Mrs. Mookmanee, it looks like
Ms. Mika is having a problem.

41
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:39,080
Children's problems should be handled
by the children themselves.

42
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:44,120
My mother taught me that

43
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,320
if someone does something to you,

44
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,040
you return it.

45
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,400
It splashed on you too, right?

46
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,080
Yeah. I'm soaked.

47
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:15,840
What a very entertaining performance.

48
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:21,040
Today is a special day,
Ms. Mika's birthday.

49
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:24,160
May I invite everyone

50
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,960
to raise a glass
and toast our lovely birthday girl.

51
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:31,080
All together, cheers!

52
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:34,720
You lowlife. How dare someone like you
wish me happy birthday?

53
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:38,120
Someone at your level
doesn't even deserve to look at me.

54
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,760
That's right.

55
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:52,120
- Yeah.
- Right?

56
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,800
Mr. Rachen, let's drink.

57
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,520
- Yes.
- Sure.

58
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:05,160
I've always wanted to try this wine
that costs tens of thousands per bottle.

59
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,600
So this is how it tastes.

60
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,840
It's delicious.

61
00:06:12,520 --> 00:06:13,520
Thank you.

62
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:31,280
You ruined my birthday cake.
It's your fault!

63
00:06:34,160 --> 00:06:36,240
Hey. What are you doing?

64
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:38,240
- Please, don't do this.
- Let her go.

65
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,560
Hey. Hey.

66
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:46,360
You wanna eat expensive things that much?
Fine. I'll donate some to you.

67
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,160
Eat it. What are you staring at?

68
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,840
Ms. Mika,

69
00:06:58,440 --> 00:07:00,720
I apologize.

70
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:03,840
Please have mercy.
Please don't take this any further.

71
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:06,760
I didn't start it. You all did.

72
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:09,240
And you spilled wine on my dress.

73
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:11,920
You were drunk
and not watching where you stepped,

74
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,480
then you blamed my friend.

75
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,120
Pakbung, stop.

76
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,720
You fell into your own cake.

77
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:23,800
You lost face, so you took it out
on someone you could push around.

78
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:28,840
Go ahead and film it. Film everything

79
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:31,200
and share it.

80
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:34,600
Let everyone see how Ms. Mika

81
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,840
bullies and oppresses poor people.

82
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:40,440
Go ahead. Bully me!

83
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:42,160
- You!
- Mika.

84
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:47,120
Don't make this a big issue.

85
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:53,480
I taught you that if someone
doesn't consent, don't force them.

86
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,720
There are many other ways
to make someone pay.

87
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:58,600
Call the lawyer.

88
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,680
- Yes, ma'am.
- What?

89
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:05,040
The event was ruined
due to staff negligence.

90
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,320
I will sue for damages.

91
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:35,799
Mrs. Mookmanee, please. I beg you.

92
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:39,320
Please don't do that. Please don't sue me.

93
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:42,720
I have no money.

94
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,680
My daughter's birthday was ruined.

95
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,520
Her feelings were hurt.

96
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:49,880
I can't let this go

97
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:54,880
unless you make
my daughter feel satisfied.

98
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:59,200
If Mika is okay, I'll drop it.

99
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:05,240
If I eat it, this will end, right?

100
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,760
Maybe.

101
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:13,160
Try it and see if I change my mind.

102
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:34,880
Eat it.

103
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,160
Happy birthday, Ms. Mika.

104
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:56,360
How dare you ruin Ms. Mika's birthday?

105
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,320
Dad?

106
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,520
What are you doing here?

107
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:13,400
Get out. Leave this place right now. Go.

108
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,760
Did you cut the power?

109
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,040
Yes.

110
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:37,800
Why?

111
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,480
To help you.

112
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:43,760
Why did you turn off the lights?
Why did you pull me out?

113
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,320
Wait, Pakbung. Calm down.
Get yourself together.

114
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,520
If you go back in, it will only get worse.

115
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:53,520
Ms. Mika won't let this go,
let alone Mrs. Mookmanee.

116
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,320
She has power and connections.

117
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,080
If you fight back, it will escalate.

118
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,720
They're worse than you think.

119
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,480
I saw my father.

120
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,160
The father
I've wanted to see for ten years,

121
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:14,480
I wanted him to come back to me,

122
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:17,440
to be with me and Kanah.

123
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:20,760
He was there. He protected that girl.

124
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:22,960
He slapped me.

125
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:57,760
Uh, Mrs. Mook. Mrs. Mook.

126
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:04,120
I'm sorry. When I saw that girl come in
and ruin Ms. Mika's birthday,

127
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:07,560
I couldn't take it. I lost control

128
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,240
and had to teach that kid a lesson.

129
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,200
That girl called you Dad.

130
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:15,160
Why would I be her dad, Mrs. Mook?

131
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:19,080
I'm single. I've never been married.
I've never had a child.

132
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,920
I've never loved anyone but you.

133
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,680
Yongyut, if you want to stay with me,

134
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:26,720
don't do anything I haven't ordered.

135
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:30,080
I'm sorry.

136
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:32,600
If you want to leave the past behind,
cut it off completely.

137
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:36,800
If I find out that you went in there
to protect your daughter,

138
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:38,480
it's over for both of you.

139
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:51,160
Did you find him?

140
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:58,480
It has to be him. Try searching again.

141
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:00,000
Search everywhere.

142
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:07,040
Why did Trai come here?

143
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,800
And he was in a server uniform.

144
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,720
Or did he come to see Dad?

145
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,600
A friend of my friend who has met Mr. Trai

146
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:26,240
said he saw him
at Ms. Mika's birthday party.

147
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:28,320
Prarop and I have checked.

148
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:31,920
This clip is the clearest one.
I captured it and adjusted the color.

149
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,120
It really is Mr. Trai.

150
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,320
Bring him back no matter what.

151
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,600
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

152
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:57,000
- Bung!
- Bung, how are you?

153
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,400
Are you okay?

154
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:02,520
Did you get hurt? Huh?

155
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:06,120
Niuniu told me everything. Petch is
really upset, so she's staying with him.

156
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:11,200
Too bad I wasn't there. Otherwise,
I would have smashed a wine bottle

157
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:14,040
on that spoiled girl's face
and rubbed her head into the cake.

158
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,600
I'd take off my shoes
and slap her in the face with them.

159
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,160
She'd be finished.

160
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,440
Brutal but agreed.

161
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:28,760
- Did Niuniu tell you who I ran into?
- Who?

162
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:32,800
What? Are you keeping secrets?

163
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:36,640
If you're hiding things from me,
you could die anytime.

164
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,960
I'm not dead yet.

165
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:42,640
I can still pay your tuition.

166
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:46,840
Then try dying. I will dig you up myself.

167
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:51,000
You already look like
you crawled out of a grave.

168
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,320
How about this?

169
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:57,360
We hire Noy and the guys to deal
with that spoiled girl and her mother.

170
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:02,400
Are you crazy?
Why risk ourselves for people like that?

171
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:07,120
They can look down on us,
but we do not have to sink to their level.

172
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,480
Then black magic.

173
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:12,240
Conjure buffalo hide into their guts.

174
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:16,000
Are you crazy, Samlee?

175
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:19,440
I know you're angry. I am too.

176
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:20,880
But there has to be another way.

177
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:23,200
Yes. There has to be another way.

178
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,360
But maybe Pakbung should shower first.

179
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:30,920
Right. Go shower.

180
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:04,000
I'd like an antibiotic cream
that reduces inflammation

181
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:05,880
but doesn't leave scars.

182
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,560
My friend…

183
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:12,480
My friend fell
and has a small scrape on her hand.

184
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:14,400
Sure.

185
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:21,440
Anyway, have you called your friend yet?

186
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:25,840
My friend? Pakbung?

187
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:29,440
Oh? Someone came
looking for you the other day.

188
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:32,720
I already told Pakbung
and gave her his business card.

189
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:50,240
<i>He said there would be</i>
<i>a reward for information,</i>

190
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:52,880
<i>so I told Pakbung to try contacting him.</i>

191
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:04,000
Mr. Trai! Mr. Trai!

192
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:05,440
Prarop?

193
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:07,880
I am sorry, Mr. Trai.

194
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:10,480
Easy, Mr. Trai…

195
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:30,760
Hey, Mr. Trai!

196
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,360
- Wait, Mr. Trai!
- Let go, Lee, Rop!

197
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,360
Let me go!

198
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:35,640
Please hold on.
Mr. Tritot wants to see you.

199
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,960
I don't want to see him. I don't.

200
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:40,080
Let go!

201
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,160
Block the way.

202
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:49,200
Mr. Trai, please see Mr. Tritot.
I'm begging you.

203
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,840
Please calm down. Calm down.

204
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,240
Calm down…

205
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,200
Even if you run,

206
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:59,560
Mr. Tritot will find you anyway.

207
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:07,480
Wait. Did Pakbung tell you where I was?

208
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:11,600
I already paid the caretaker fee.

209
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:13,000
Don't worry.

210
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:15,120
Huh? Caretaker fee?

211
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:17,400
- Yes…
- How much?

212
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:18,400
100,000?

213
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,880
Yeah.

214
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:25,160
When I was leaving for school,
someone asked about Trai.

215
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:27,920
Excuse me, do you know this person?

216
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,240
That's Trai.

217
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,320
Do you know him?

218
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,560
- I don't know him.
- Wait, wait.

219
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,080
- Please calm down.
- Wait.

220
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:41,200
He's my younger brother.
He ran away after fighting with Dad.

221
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:43,960
If you know where he is, please tell us.

222
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:47,800
But I didn't tell them Trai was here.
They asked for my account number,

223
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:50,560
so I sent the QR code, just in case.

224
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:54,160
They really transferred the money
and said it was a caretaker fee.

225
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:59,080
Hey. Is Mr. Trai that rich?
Just a few days of service

226
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,520
for 100,000.

227
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:03,920
It's "only" 100,000.

228
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:10,920
Pakbung, wait for me. Hey.

229
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,640
Wait for me. Wait.

230
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,840
- Mr. Trai.
- Mr. Trai.

231
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:19,040
Pakbung would never take only 100,000.

232
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,640
You hurt her, didn't you?

233
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:22,560
- No, we didn't.
- No.

234
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:24,120
Fists, sticks, or guns, huh?

235
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,560
Mr. Trai, we are not thugs.

236
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:28,880
But you chopped the back of my neck?
It still hurts.

237
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:32,400
- No, Mr. Trai. We…
- We really did pay them.

238
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,120
There was no assault, for sure.

239
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:39,000
She said 300,000.
How could she take only one?

240
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:43,360
If you were going to sell our friendship,
you should've asked more than this.

241
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,040
I can pay more.

242
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:53,840
If you think 100,000
is too little for your value,

243
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,320
I can arrange it.

244
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,320
Keep your money to buy something else.

245
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:07,440
When something has value,
you pay to get it.

246
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:12,000
If you're counting on freebies like usual,
you'll probably only get a bite or two.

247
00:20:12,080 --> 00:20:13,560
Or you’ve never gotten even a bite?

248
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,920
If you want what I have,
if you want what I get,

249
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:23,480
then get as rich as I am,

250
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:25,880
have as much power as I do.

251
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:28,400
Don't act like a pathetic loser.

252
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:31,480
The moment anything happens,
you run and cry.

253
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:35,720
And just like that,
everything gets taken from your life.

254
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,640
Mom.

255
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,520
Have you greeted your son yet?

256
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:54,400
Haven't seen each other
in a long time, right?

257
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:57,680
You must have missed each other so much.

258
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,440
We're all here today. Father,

259
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:04,240
mother, and son.

260
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:09,040
What a perfect family.

261
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:36,440
You married Darin
to punish me, didn't you?

262
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,120
I sent you abroad for three years,

263
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:43,600
and you were still stubborn, asking
for Darin all the time. Are you insane?

264
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:46,280
Because I made her suffer.

265
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:48,440
I caused it,
so I have to take responsibility.

266
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,120
Responsibility for what?

267
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,760
Do you know the victim was a doctor?

268
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:54,760
People cursed you all over the country.

269
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:56,160
You weren't driving.
Why did you take the blame?

270
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:59,160
It was because of me, Dad. It was my car.

271
00:21:59,760 --> 00:22:01,200
I forced Darin to drink.

272
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:02,880
But you were not the one driving.

273
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,520
And someone that drunk
shouldn't be driving.

274
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:10,680
Are you going to trade your whole life,
your future, for one woman?

275
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:14,040
And you call that love? Stupid.

276
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:17,720
Any feeling that drags you down
is not love.

277
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:21,400
It's stupidity, obsession, foolishness.
Idiot!

278
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:27,720
Then what was actually
behind everything you did to me?

279
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:31,200
Good intentions? Or love?

280
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:36,600
A love that only forces
and controls me all the time?

281
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:41,200
A love that is ready to kill me
the moment I disobey you?

282
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:48,080
Good. Someone like you needs
to get hurt sometimes,

283
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,640
so you will stop being stupid.

284
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:56,640
So you really do want to kill me.

285
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:05,080
You're so naive.

286
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:08,520
Someone as naive as you
will never keep up with Darin's game.

287
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:10,200
This world is brutal, Trai.

288
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:12,320
There is no place for the weak.

289
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:16,160
That is why I taught you, handled you,

290
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:17,640
so you would be stronger

291
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:20,640
and stand higher
where no one could drag you down.

292
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:25,240
Remember this. I will never
allow anyone to destroy you.

293
00:23:25,320 --> 00:23:27,840
Did you ever ask me even once
if I wanted that?

294
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:32,280
Stop forcing your love on me.
I'm going to die because of it.

295
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:46,000
Don't go up yet.
Mr. Tritot is talking to his son.

296
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:52,480
You rushed here because you heard
Trai is back, didn't you?

297
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,240
Please wait.

298
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:58,360
Father and son need to talk in private.

299
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,800
Outsiders should not interfere.

300
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,280
If you're angry
because your lovers kicked you out,

301
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:07,080
then go scream in the bathroom.
Don't take it out on me.

302
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:11,040
It's annoying.

303
00:24:20,320 --> 00:24:22,440
- Let's go, Mr. Trai.
- Mr. Trai.

304
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,840
- Let's go.
- Mr. Trai, come with us.

305
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:26,920
- Please don't, Mr. Trai.
- Please don't. Come with us.

306
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,600
- Mr. Trai.
- Put him in the room.

307
00:24:29,680 --> 00:24:31,920
Guard the door and don't let him come out.

308
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:34,360
Let him calm down in there.

309
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,600
- You cannot force me.
- Why not?

310
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:41,840
- Take him.
- Hey. What's wrong with you again?

311
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:47,400
Here. Your favorite son is here.

312
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:49,840
Rachen obeys everything you say.

313
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:51,440
Let him do it for me.

314
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,840
The inheritance, the business, all of it.

315
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:55,320
Let him do it.

316
00:24:57,080 --> 00:24:59,440
You want it so badly? Then take it.

317
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:01,800
I will transfer
my status as his son to you.

318
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:04,640
Trai, you are my only son,

319
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,600
and that will never change.

320
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:09,320
But I don't want to be that.

321
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,480
What kind of parenting is this?
You treat me like a dog.

322
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:14,440
If you could put a collar on me,
you would have done it.

323
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:19,560
I don't want a father like you.
Stop forcing me. Stop hurting me!

324
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:21,960
- I'm telling you, stop hurting me!
- Trai!

325
00:25:22,040 --> 00:25:23,840
- I barely have a life now.
- Go.

326
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,600
- Take him.
- Deal with him.

327
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:26,520
Take him.

328
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:27,480
Take him!

329
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:29,680
- Mr. Trai, let's go.
- Let's get to your room.

330
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:30,720
- Please, Mr. Trai.
- No.

331
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:32,880
- Please, Mr. Trai.
- Enough, please.

332
00:25:32,960 --> 00:25:34,520
- Enough, please.
- Let me go.

333
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:35,680
Please, Mr. Trai.

334
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:36,720
Let's go inside.

335
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:40,080
Dad, are you okay?

336
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:41,960
I'm fine.

337
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:47,000
I'm fine.

338
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:50,640
Dad.

339
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,480
Calm down.

340
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:18,160
Wow. This is Mr. Trai's house?

341
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:20,040
Damn.

342
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:23,680
Now I know why you said
it was only 100,000.

343
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:26,880
He wouldn't give me money that easily.

344
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:28,880
Something must have happened.

345
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,400
Hey, Pakbung!

346
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:45,720
- What's the matter?
- I'm here to see Mr. Trai.

347
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,600
I'm his friend.

348
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:53,200
You? A friend of Mr. Trai?
I don't think so.

349
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:56,600
Hey. Why are you looking down on us?

350
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:59,160
Go live.

351
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:06,040
Fine. Let's do it.

352
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:09,160
Everyone, help us out.
I'm here with a friend,

353
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:12,120
and we're coming to see a friend
at a friend's house, and this guy

354
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,840
is insulting us.

355
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,080
Hey.

356
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:16,400
Give it back.

357
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:18,200
- Give it back!
- You can't film here.

358
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:19,600
Let go!

359
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:21,520
Where are you going?

360
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:22,800
Hey! Pakbung!

361
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:28,520
Help, everyone. He's using force.

362
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:30,200
- He's assaulting us.
- Give it to me.

363
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:31,760
- Give it to me.
- Stop.

364
00:27:31,840 --> 00:27:33,160
Stop.

365
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:39,120
Why use violence? You can talk nicely.

366
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:46,640
Are you okay?

367
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:02,960
I remember you,
from Ms. Mika's birthday party.

368
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:04,280
That was you, right?

369
00:28:06,720 --> 00:28:07,600
I'm here to see Mr. Trai.

370
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,240
You're Trai's friend?

371
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:14,720
Yes. Mr. Trai stayed
at Pakbung's place for several days.

372
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:21,120
Trai is inside. I'll take you in myself.

373
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:24,200
You can't.

374
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:26,600
Mr. Trai won't allow any guests.

375
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:57,320
When are you going
to stop causing problems, Trai?

376
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:01,680
Isn't it you
who has problem with me, huh?!

377
00:29:02,600 --> 00:29:04,680
Dad loves you. He cares about you.

378
00:29:04,760 --> 00:29:06,360
Try being a good son for once.

379
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:08,360
What kind of love is that?!

380
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:11,080
He stole my girlfriend, and now,
he's locking me up like a prisoner.

381
00:29:11,160 --> 00:29:13,680
He sacrificed for you. For you!

382
00:29:13,760 --> 00:29:15,320
So you'd finally open your eyes.

383
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:17,920
You want a cheap woman
like Darin as your wife?

384
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:25,040
If you’re so much like Dad,
why weren’t you born his real son?

385
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:31,840
Why don't you die then?!
So Dad will have only me.

386
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:33,600
You want to kill me that badly?

387
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:36,280
Go on. Do it.

388
00:29:37,080 --> 00:29:39,960
If I'm gone, you get everything,
money, Dad's love.

389
00:29:40,040 --> 00:29:41,960
You've been waiting for a chance
to kill me this whole time.

390
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:44,680
Come on. Come on, Bro. Go ahead.

391
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:46,600
Do it. Kill me!

392
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:53,760
I want you dead.

393
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:55,920
I want you dead!

394
00:29:58,080 --> 00:30:01,680
But if you die, Dad will suffer even more.

395
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:10,440
You can't die yet, Trai.

396
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:24,840
Mr. Trai said you wouldn't be satisfied
with only 100,000 baht.

397
00:30:27,840 --> 00:30:28,680
Sign here.

398
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:32,920
"The recipient is prohibited

399
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:36,680
from contacting Mr. Trai
Bowornmongkolphong through any channel."

400
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:41,280
"The recipient's prohibited from involving
themselves in any way with Mr. Trai…"

401
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:46,600
This is like a drama. A messy romance
with a mafia prince or something.

402
00:30:51,520 --> 00:30:53,560
Did Mr. Trai tell you
to write this contract?

403
00:30:53,640 --> 00:30:54,840
Yes.

404
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:56,720
And he told you to bring me this check?

405
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:58,320
Correct.

406
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:06,560
Please. I'm just poor, not stupid.

407
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:10,960
That kind of person
would never give me money.

408
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:13,000
He wouldn't give me even one baht.

409
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:15,680
So what did you do to him? Kidnap him?

410
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:17,360
Detain him?

411
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:18,600
Or did you kill him?

412
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:24,160
You talk exactly like him.
What kind of people do you think we are?

413
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:27,560
If Mr. Trai is fine,
then let him come talk to me.

414
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:31,000
You lived with him for a few days,
and you think you know him well?

415
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:33,640
And how long have you been with him?

416
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:36,080
You still don't know what he's like?

417
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:42,600
I want the money so bad.

418
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:44,280
If you're giving it, then give it.

419
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:46,320
But I'm not gonna sign this contract.

420
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:49,920
And tell the person
who ordered you here this.

421
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:54,120
If you want me to stop getting involved
with Mr. Trai, then pay more.

422
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,200
Pakbung.

423
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:07,000
100,000 is already a lot.

424
00:32:08,200 --> 00:32:09,480
I'd take 10,000 and be done.

425
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,400
You're leaving me again?

426
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:37,400
Who left who?

427
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:39,680
Trai.

428
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:41,520
As far as I remember,

429
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,040
you left me to marry my father.

430
00:32:44,120 --> 00:32:46,280
Trai, can you listen to me first?

431
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:47,800
I'm listening. Go ahead.

432
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:52,120
Your father forced me. I had no choice.

433
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:55,120
Don't tell me you had no choice.
You did. You just didn't choose it.

434
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,240
The other path was poor and hard,

435
00:32:58,920 --> 00:33:01,440
so you sold your dignity,

436
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:03,840
sold yourself.

437
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:07,520
Three years.

438
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:11,480
Three years, Trai.
You never cared about me at all.

439
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:18,280
If that day, you hadn't run off abroad…

440
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:20,800
No.

441
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:24,800
If that night, you hadn't made me drink,

442
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:28,960
would my life have ended up like this?

443
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:37,080
Drink it! Drink it! Drink it!

444
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,320
Bottoms up. Bottoms up.

445
00:33:49,760 --> 00:33:51,760
- Are you leaving?
- Alright, get home safe.

446
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:53,920
- We haven't finished it yet.
- Get home safe.

447
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:56,480
- Get home safe.
- Let's go.

448
00:33:56,560 --> 00:34:00,160
Trai, I'll drive.

449
00:34:00,240 --> 00:34:01,400
Let's go.

450
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:26,320
It's because of you
that I ended up like this.

451
00:34:26,920 --> 00:34:28,360
Because you were weak.

452
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,960
You never protected me.

453
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:35,120
The day I got sued, the day I got fired,

454
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:38,840
the day I had no job, no money,
where were you?!

455
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,719
Where were you?!

456
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:46,440
You're not me. You'll never understand.

457
00:34:46,520 --> 00:34:48,080
You would never understand.

458
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:54,400
And what if you had
the chance to choose again?

459
00:34:57,720 --> 00:35:00,360
That other path you said didn't exist,
it's right here.

460
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:04,560
Come with me. Leave everything.
Leave the past behind and start over.

461
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:07,520
Will you go with me?

462
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:29,360
But all I have is what you see.

463
00:35:32,160 --> 00:35:35,560
Just me and my heart, none of Dad's money.

464
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:50,360
So you're thinking of having an affair
with your own father's wife?

465
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:53,960
This is my house.

466
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:02,720
If I could be a little worse,

467
00:36:03,760 --> 00:36:06,040
I'd have gone around and used
the same woman as you already.

468
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:10,320
But too bad.
This is a house, not a brothel.

469
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:13,640
And I'm not like you.

470
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:15,760
- Trai!
- Don't worry.

471
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:19,160
I'm not going to mess with your woman.

472
00:36:24,240 --> 00:36:27,160
But if your woman comes after me first,

473
00:36:28,040 --> 00:36:29,920
then that's on her.

474
00:36:31,160 --> 00:36:33,400
Call it karma catching up with you.

475
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:41,360
Look at how confident you are, Trai.

476
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:54,680
Is Trai misunderstanding something?

477
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,760
Tell him, sweetheart.

478
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:05,080
Mr. Trai.

479
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:06,880
Mr. Trai.

480
00:37:06,960 --> 00:37:08,280
Ms. Darin doesn't want your help.

481
00:37:10,480 --> 00:37:12,320
Let me go.

482
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:28,240
Your mother still isn't well,
is she, Darin?

483
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:32,120
Let go of me. Let go!

484
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:56,800
If you still want money from me,
then stop throwing yourself to my son.

485
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:49,400
How is Petch doing?

486
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:54,120
The doctor already pumped his stomach.

487
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:58,280
They have to monitor him,
but Petch still hasn't woken up yet.

488
00:38:58,360 --> 00:39:00,760
A letter from Mrs. Mookmanee's lawyer.

489
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:03,760
They're suing us
for 20 million baht in damages.

490
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:05,560
20 million baht?

491
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,840
This is obviously harassment.

492
00:39:13,920 --> 00:39:16,160
Petch was so stressed out.

493
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:18,640
He downed a whole pack of sleeping pills.

494
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:20,840
Good thing Samlee and I saw it,

495
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:22,800
so we called an ambulance.

496
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:38,560
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

497
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:40,040
Good afternoon.

498
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:46,360
You didn't have to come in person.
I was going to bring the documents to you.

499
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,720
I just wanted to see how my company…

500
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:55,640
I mean, the company
I hold shares in, operates.

501
00:39:57,800 --> 00:40:01,200
And will Mika get bored, having to
sit here listening to adults talk numbers?

502
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:07,280
If I were bored, I wouldn't have come.

503
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:10,800
I came because there's
something interesting here.

504
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:15,080
Mom wanted me to come see for myself

505
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:16,920
whether I like it or not.

506
00:40:19,200 --> 00:40:20,680
So far, I'm okay with it, Mom.

507
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:27,840
Mr. Rachen, do you have time?
I want Mika to learn how things work here.

508
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:35,000
Of course.
I'll take good care of Ms. Mika.

509
00:40:35,080 --> 00:40:36,560
You don't have to worry.

510
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:45,560
Mr. Rachen looks good. He seems like
a great match for our Ms. Mika.

511
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,560
I mean your Ms. Mika.

512
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:57,640
I like that he's capable.

513
00:40:57,720 --> 00:41:01,440
A son of a mistress being ambitious
enough to come this far is impressive.

514
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:03,680
But if Mika doesn't like him,
I won't force her.

515
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:05,800
Ms. Mika is really lucky

516
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:09,240
to have a mother who loves her
and who is kind like you.

517
00:41:11,200 --> 00:41:13,800
Please wait here for a moment.
I'll go get the car.

518
00:41:16,080 --> 00:41:17,360
Mrs. Mookmanee.

519
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:22,400
You're suing Petch
for 20 million baht in damages.

520
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:26,680
Petch overdosed on sleeping pills.
He's in the hospital right now.

521
00:41:28,800 --> 00:41:29,920
Are you just going to stand there?

522
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:33,040
Uh, right.

523
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:34,480
I'm sorry.

524
00:41:36,560 --> 00:41:40,200
It's all my fault.
I was arrogant and cocky,

525
00:41:40,280 --> 00:41:42,320
so you and your daughter got upset.

526
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:44,800
If you're angry at me, then come after me.

527
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:46,880
Demand whatever you want from me.

528
00:41:46,960 --> 00:41:50,360
But please withdraw
the lawsuit against Petch.

529
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:52,960
Everything has a price.

530
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:56,680
Even if you can't afford it,
that's not my problem.

531
00:41:56,760 --> 00:41:58,640
I'm sorry I was born poor,

532
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:02,760
with no money, no way to compare to you.

533
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:05,640
And I was stupid and reckless enough
to get in your way.

534
00:42:06,240 --> 00:42:10,440
But you're rich. You have everything.

535
00:42:10,520 --> 00:42:11,920
You have power.

536
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:14,560
Can't you show us a little mercy?

537
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:22,240
Mrs. Mookmanee, cornering us like this
is the same as killing us alive.

538
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:32,160
So you're recording this.

539
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:46,120
She's not recording. It's live.

540
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:48,320
There are over a thousand viewers.

541
00:42:48,400 --> 00:42:51,240
If your banking partners see this,
it'll be bad.

542
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:55,480
Only a thousand people?

543
00:42:55,560 --> 00:42:59,080
I know a thousand people
can't do anything to you.

544
00:42:59,160 --> 00:43:02,600
But there has to be someone
among them who hates you.

545
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:11,040
You think doing this

546
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:13,800
is smart?

547
00:43:13,880 --> 00:43:16,040
I just want you
to withdraw the lawsuit against Petch.

548
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:19,760
Loyal but stupid.

549
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:23,640
People like you have ruined
so many bosses already, you know.

550
00:43:23,720 --> 00:43:24,800
I'm not…

551
00:43:26,480 --> 00:43:27,680
You're picking a fight with my mom?

552
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:33,320
- Ms. Mika.
- Let go.

553
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:35,320
- Ms. Mika.
- Mika.

554
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:55,760
Come here. Come here.

555
00:43:56,360 --> 00:43:57,400
Let go of me.

556
00:43:58,280 --> 00:43:59,320
Go.

557
00:44:06,440 --> 00:44:07,400
Pakbung.

558
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:08,520
PARKING AREA

559
00:44:08,600 --> 00:44:10,440
Put this on it, so it won't swell up.

560
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:14,360
It doesn't hurt as much
as when you slapped me that day.

561
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:16,600
Come on, Pakbung.

562
00:44:16,680 --> 00:44:19,960
Can't you see?
What I did that day was to help you.

563
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:24,600
Help? By pretending you didn't know me?

564
00:44:25,400 --> 00:44:27,400
Acting like you didn't recognize
your own kid?

565
00:44:28,640 --> 00:44:32,720
I had to.
I'm working for Mrs. Mookmanee now.

566
00:44:32,800 --> 00:44:36,960
She's my boss. I don't want trouble.

567
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:38,520
How much is she paying you?

568
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:42,120
- Why are you asking?
- How much?

569
00:44:42,800 --> 00:44:45,560
Hey, Pakbung. I don't have much either.

570
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:47,600
I'm living paycheck to paycheck too.

571
00:44:47,680 --> 00:44:50,120
I'm asking

572
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:54,280
because I want to know how much money
it took to buy fatherhood from you.

573
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:59,520
Tens of thousands? Hundreds of thousands?

574
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:06,160
If it's less than that, that's disgusting.
Dumping your kids for a few thousand.

575
00:45:06,240 --> 00:45:09,280
Okay, Pakbung. It's my fault.

576
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:13,040
I didn't dare go to you
and your brother because of this.

577
00:45:16,960 --> 00:45:20,040
I'm not a good man.
I can't provide for a family.

578
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:23,840
You can hate me all you want.
But don't waste your tears

579
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:25,960
on trash like me anymore.

580
00:45:26,560 --> 00:45:27,480
Just live our own lives.

581
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:31,880
I'll go now. Okay. Goodbye.

582
00:45:32,480 --> 00:45:34,720
That only worked on me
when I was in eighth grade.

583
00:45:36,240 --> 00:45:37,360
You're still a little kid--

584
00:45:37,440 --> 00:45:39,760
Enough. Stop acting.

585
00:45:39,840 --> 00:45:43,880
You can go be with whoever you want,
wherever you want. I don't care anymore.

586
00:45:44,720 --> 00:45:48,120
But you still have to take responsibility
for the debt you created.

587
00:45:49,200 --> 00:45:50,040
What are you gonna do?

588
00:45:50,720 --> 00:45:54,320
I won't do anything. But Mr. Song might.

589
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:16,600
What the heck is this?

590
00:46:16,680 --> 00:46:18,480
Being poor isn't enough.
My dad even ditched me too.

591
00:46:18,560 --> 00:46:21,320
In this life or the next,
don't ever let me see you again.

592
00:46:28,480 --> 00:46:29,840
Mika.

593
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:30,760
- Come here.
- Hey.

594
00:46:30,840 --> 00:46:31,760
Let me go.

595
00:46:31,840 --> 00:46:34,280
You're trying to ruin my mom's reputation?

596
00:46:34,880 --> 00:46:36,080
What do you want?

597
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:41,320
What? Hey.

598
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:42,440
That's my phone.

599
00:46:47,080 --> 00:46:49,080
You punks. Let me go!

600
00:46:49,160 --> 00:46:50,720
You bastard. I said let me go.

601
00:46:50,800 --> 00:46:53,520
I'm going to use the media
to bring all of you down!

602
00:46:54,160 --> 00:46:57,160
Hey, you know what makes us different?

603
00:46:57,920 --> 00:47:01,720
I have friends with power, not cowards

604
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:07,040
who cry all the time or swallow pills
to kill themselves like your friend.

605
00:47:07,680 --> 00:47:12,280
And I have a mother who backs me up,
who cleans up every problem for me.

606
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:14,040
You know what it all starts with?

607
00:47:15,840 --> 00:47:16,680
Money.

608
00:47:16,760 --> 00:47:18,640
Hey, don't move.

609
00:47:18,720 --> 00:47:19,960
I'm gonna use the media to…

610
00:47:21,840 --> 00:47:22,880
Get up.

611
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:29,000
Come here.

612
00:48:02,400 --> 00:48:03,880
Mr. Trai.

613
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:06,040
Watch out!

614
00:48:10,080 --> 00:48:11,360
Mr. Trai.

615
00:48:17,080 --> 00:48:18,120
Let's go.

616
00:48:18,200 --> 00:48:20,120
Let's go. Get up.

617
00:48:27,040 --> 00:48:28,080
Run.

618
00:48:32,640 --> 00:48:33,920
- My phone.
- Let her go.

619
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:56,560
Does it hurt?

620
00:49:01,480 --> 00:49:04,240
How did you know Mrs. Mookmanee
was at my dad's company?

621
00:49:04,320 --> 00:49:06,720
That brat posted it on Instagram.

622
00:49:08,640 --> 00:49:11,080
So you went in alone
without thinking it through?

623
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:12,560
Pakbung, don't do that again.

624
00:49:12,640 --> 00:49:15,200
Don't confront
Mrs. Mookmanee head-on like that.

625
00:49:15,280 --> 00:49:18,600
How could I just do nothing?
Petch almost died.

626
00:49:18,680 --> 00:49:20,960
And then they came after me too.

627
00:49:24,120 --> 00:49:25,440
My phone.

628
00:49:26,480 --> 00:49:29,360
My phone… They recorded me.

629
00:49:30,360 --> 00:49:33,680
I'll use it as evidence,
post it, expose all of them.

630
00:49:34,400 --> 00:49:35,720
Mika took it.

631
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:44,840
She's rich, and she still steals my phone?

632
00:49:44,920 --> 00:49:46,520
It cost over 10,000.

633
00:49:46,600 --> 00:49:50,000
Don't think having a clip
means you can take them down.

634
00:49:50,080 --> 00:49:51,960
Like your livestream earlier today.

635
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:54,800
Mrs. Mookmanee's legal team
already handled it.

636
00:49:54,880 --> 00:49:56,960
How can she be that untouchable?

637
00:49:57,040 --> 00:50:01,120
It's not much. She owns shares
in both major and minor media outlets.

638
00:50:01,200 --> 00:50:03,560
She's got friends who own mobile networks.

639
00:50:04,320 --> 00:50:08,040
And she has connections with the CEO
of the app you livestreamed on earlier.

640
00:50:08,120 --> 00:50:09,880
Damn it!

641
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:20,520
That's exactly what you looked like
trying to fight Mrs. Mookmanee.

642
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:25,120
You almost broke your leg,
but the table leg barely moved.

643
00:50:29,600 --> 00:50:33,880
There has to be a way. Right now,
we need to calm down and think together.

644
00:50:35,800 --> 00:50:36,640
We?

645
00:50:51,360 --> 00:50:53,880
I didn't tell anyone you were here.

646
00:50:53,960 --> 00:50:57,680
I knew it.
100,000 or 200,000 can't buy you.

647
00:51:00,280 --> 00:51:01,760
If it was 400,000 or 500,000,
I might consider it.

648
00:51:03,000 --> 00:51:04,400
Take that.

649
00:51:10,960 --> 00:51:13,120
You didn't run back home
on your own, did you?

650
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:15,000
You think I left you?

651
00:51:15,960 --> 00:51:19,520
Maybe you got bored playing poor.

652
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:22,840
It was probably at Mika's birthday party.

653
00:51:23,680 --> 00:51:26,440
Lee and Prarop must've figured out
where I was. That's how they found me.

654
00:51:26,520 --> 00:51:30,240
I saved your life once.
Today, you saved mine.

655
00:51:30,320 --> 00:51:31,760
We're even.

656
00:51:32,360 --> 00:51:34,840
From now on, it's just friendship.

657
00:51:34,920 --> 00:51:38,040
Heart for heart. Nothing owed.

658
00:51:46,960 --> 00:51:47,800
Deal.

659
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:57,440
But the 100,000 you gave me,
consider it a gift then.

660
00:51:58,440 --> 00:52:00,000
A gift, my ass.

661
00:52:00,080 --> 00:52:01,000
Hey.

662
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:06,640
You're still greedy. Come here.

663
00:52:10,680 --> 00:52:11,840
Be gentle.

664
00:52:28,880 --> 00:52:30,480
You're so tough, huh?

665
00:52:31,800 --> 00:52:33,040
Get up.

666
00:52:33,120 --> 00:52:35,560
Go ahead.

667
00:52:36,720 --> 00:52:38,520
- Trai?
- What the hell?!

668
00:53:00,880 --> 00:53:02,720
I've got work this afternoon.

669
00:53:03,320 --> 00:53:05,760
Look after Petch for me.

670
00:53:05,840 --> 00:53:08,080
Yeah, of course.

671
00:53:08,160 --> 00:53:10,240
Petch has helped me a lot.

672
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:14,800
Back when I didn't have a job,
he was the one who gave me jobs.

673
00:53:16,120 --> 00:53:20,640
I'm just scared that if he finds out
all his gigs got canceled…

674
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:22,960
He can't find out.

675
00:53:23,040 --> 00:53:25,160
How long can we keep it hidden?

676
00:53:26,080 --> 00:53:28,280
That woman won't let us go.

677
00:53:28,360 --> 00:53:32,320
She sued us, and on top of that,
she got all of Petch's work canceled too.

678
00:53:32,920 --> 00:53:35,120
So we really can't fight them at all?

679
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:38,040
Revenge is for people with power.

680
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:42,640
Then we need power first
if we want to fight them, right?

681
00:53:43,240 --> 00:53:46,640
But before you get power,
you need money first.

682
00:53:46,720 --> 00:53:48,280
When's the next doctor's appointment?

683
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:49,800
Next week, Boss.

684
00:54:07,200 --> 00:54:08,280
Pakbung!

685
00:54:08,360 --> 00:54:10,240
You! Stop.

686
00:54:10,840 --> 00:54:13,160
No! Don't get ahead of me!

687
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:15,080
Our speed isn't the same.
Don't go before me.

688
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:21,440
Where do you think you're going?
You won't get away.

689
00:54:21,520 --> 00:54:23,480
- You…
- Boss.

690
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:24,560
What?

691
00:54:25,520 --> 00:54:26,960
- Why am I so screwed?
- Hey.

692
00:54:27,040 --> 00:54:28,520
Hey, hey.

693
00:54:28,600 --> 00:54:32,360
Heaven really doesn't favor the guilty.
In the end, we met here.

694
00:54:32,440 --> 00:54:34,320
Where are you going?

695
00:54:39,320 --> 00:54:40,120
What happened?

696
00:54:40,200 --> 00:54:41,200
Are you hurt?

697
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:45,320
I am. It hurts a lot.

698
00:54:45,400 --> 00:54:47,800
- Could you drop me off just up ahead?
- Yes.

699
00:54:47,880 --> 00:54:48,720
Did it hit her?

700
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:50,240
No, no. It didn't.

701
00:54:52,640 --> 00:54:55,360
Where are you taking
my beloved little sister?

702
00:54:55,440 --> 00:54:56,720
You. Hey.

703
00:55:07,640 --> 00:55:10,600
You can drop me off here. Thank you.

704
00:55:13,120 --> 00:55:14,520
You're still hurt, aren't you?

705
00:55:16,040 --> 00:55:17,080
You!

706
00:55:18,120 --> 00:55:19,920
I'll take you home.

707
00:55:21,760 --> 00:55:23,400
You're Mr. Trai's brother.

708
00:55:24,200 --> 00:55:26,760
- That's all you remember?
- You're on Mrs. Mookmanee's side.

709
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:28,080
Are you going to kill me?

710
00:55:29,520 --> 00:55:31,120
They're your father's creditors, right?

711
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:36,160
Mrs. Mookmanee sent you
to dig into me, didn't she?

712
00:55:36,240 --> 00:55:38,400
One should be responsible
for the debts they create.

713
00:55:38,480 --> 00:55:40,560
Why don't you just tell them
where your father is?

714
00:55:41,640 --> 00:55:43,120
So you want to know about my dad?

715
00:55:44,920 --> 00:55:47,400
Actually, you still worry
about your father, don't you?

716
00:55:51,520 --> 00:55:57,120
Yes, the numbers might drop
next year. But let's see

717
00:55:57,200 --> 00:55:58,800
whether they still haven't gone up yet,

718
00:55:58,880 --> 00:56:01,120
- or if it's stuck at a 2.3% return.
- Dad.

719
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:02,800
What is this flight ticket?

720
00:56:04,280 --> 00:56:06,080
It's the original plan.
You'll go train with Mr. Jim.

721
00:56:06,160 --> 00:56:08,440
- No, it's not.
- It's not my plan. It never was.

722
00:56:10,120 --> 00:56:11,320
Don't you dare chop me again.

723
00:56:11,400 --> 00:56:13,320
No, Mr. Trai. I'm just escorting you out.

724
00:56:14,440 --> 00:56:16,800
Just a moment. Hey, get out.
Can't you see I'm working?

725
00:56:16,880 --> 00:56:18,280
We need to talk, Dad.

726
00:56:18,360 --> 00:56:20,480
Mr. Tritot is having a meeting
with investors right now.

727
00:56:20,560 --> 00:56:22,280
Get out. Can't you see I'm working?

728
00:56:22,880 --> 00:56:25,200
- Yes.
- I'm not flying anywhere.

729
00:56:25,280 --> 00:56:26,600
You can't force me.

730
00:56:27,280 --> 00:56:29,680
Yes. That's right.

731
00:56:45,280 --> 00:56:46,400
Trai!

732
00:56:48,120 --> 00:56:49,160
Go after him.

733
00:56:49,240 --> 00:56:50,280
Yes, sir.

734
00:56:58,440 --> 00:56:59,800
- To my mother's house.
- Yes, ma'am.

735
00:57:09,920 --> 00:57:10,760
Trai.

736
00:57:10,840 --> 00:57:12,280
If you're not getting out, shut the door.

737
00:57:16,280 --> 00:57:17,600
Mr. Trai! Where is he?

738
00:57:17,680 --> 00:57:20,400
- He's in the car.
- Mr. Trai!

739
00:57:20,480 --> 00:57:22,600
Mr. Trai. Hey, Mr. Trai!

740
00:57:23,800 --> 00:57:25,240
Mr. Trai.

741
00:57:30,200 --> 00:57:32,040
So you've lived around here
your whole life?

742
00:57:33,880 --> 00:57:38,760
No. I used to live in Heaven.
I was an angel.

743
00:57:39,360 --> 00:57:41,080
You're still funny as always.

744
00:57:44,480 --> 00:57:45,760
What do you want?

745
00:57:47,480 --> 00:57:48,880
You really don't remember me?

746
00:58:00,960 --> 00:58:02,480
Don't follow me! Get out of the way!

747
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:04,440
You! Where are you running to?!

748
00:58:05,880 --> 00:58:07,520
I'll kill you!

749
00:58:07,600 --> 00:58:09,600
Pakbung, Noy's getting crazy again.

750
00:58:09,680 --> 00:58:12,840
- Help me. Take him!
- You're dead!

751
00:58:12,920 --> 00:58:13,840
Pakbung.

752
00:58:19,840 --> 00:58:20,920
Pakbung!

753
00:58:28,200 --> 00:58:31,760
You ungrateful son.
You're more shameless than I thought.

754
00:58:31,840 --> 00:58:34,880
I hate you, Dad.

755
00:58:35,600 --> 00:58:37,160
<i>You fought with your dad again?</i>

756
00:58:37,240 --> 00:58:41,080
<i>This will probably be the last time.</i>
<i>He finally set me free.</i>

757
00:58:41,160 --> 00:58:44,360
Now they have matching phone cases?
What do you want from me?

758
00:58:45,200 --> 00:58:46,840
Why are you being this stupid?

759
00:58:46,920 --> 00:58:49,800
<i>My head hurts, not my leg.</i>
<i>Why are you holding me?</i>

760
00:58:49,880 --> 00:58:51,800
Can't I take care of you for once?

761
00:58:51,880 --> 00:58:53,960
The other day, you were kicking me out.

762
00:58:54,040 --> 00:58:55,600
<i>Today, you're happy I'm here?</i>

763
00:58:55,680 --> 00:58:58,400
How can someone change overnight, Dad?

764
00:59:04,480 --> 00:59:06,240
Mr. Trai!

765
00:59:07,240 --> 00:59:09,000
